latestPosts.caption:
1. know it’s better than your 20’s. you gain a greater sense of confidence and less worried about “people pleasing.”

2. know relationships are harder to maintain, especially if your friends are married/have kids, but relationships are much more meaningful and less superficial.

3. know things will be okay, life will always have their trials, but it never stays the same unless you want to stay stuck.

4. know that the things that you thought were important in your 20’s doesn’t seem that important, you start realizing the more important things.

5. know that you might look back and look at yourself now and say “this is not who I expected I would become,” but in your 30s you are less worried about who you thought you would become, but rather focused on who you are becoming.

6. know you will take health more seriously especially once you start seeing gray hair and even wrinkles-hence, take good care of your health and skin in your 20’s and earlier!

latestPosts.caption:
1. I’m actually Filipino, most people mistaken me for Chinese, Taiwanese, even Laos, but I took a test and I’m 99.6% Filipino! #pinoypride
2. My Master’s degree is in International Relations, for the longest time I wanted to work for the Pentagon or CIA in their counterintelligence dept. I wanted to fight off terrorism. (may still venture in doing this someday)
3. I played softball all throughout HS, wasn’t very good, but still played
4. I grew up on a farm with goats and cows and everything! Still have the farm but I mostly just visit these days.
5. I struggle with anxiety, sometimes very heavily, but I’ve learned to cope and control my thoughts and the feelings that come with anxiety, I am a strong proponent as well in drinking magnesium to help the nervous system (this is what works for me, may not work for everyone).
